# Plot by party
senators %>% 
  group_by(party_abbr, gender) %>% 
  summarise(n = n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(party_abbr, n)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = gender)) +
  ylab("# Senators") +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90)) 
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'party_abbr' (override with `.groups` argument)

# Plot by state
senators %>% 
  group_by(state, gender) %>% 
  summarise(n = n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(state, n)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = gender)) +
  ylab("# Senators") +
  theme_classic() 
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'state' (override with `.groups` argument)
